QUICK START GUIDE
=================

1. BUILD
--------
cd /workdir/kodi-renamer-go
export PATH=$PATH:~/go/bin
go build -o kodi-renamer ./cmd/kodi-renamer

2. GET API KEYS
---------------
You need at least ONE of these:

TVDB API Key:
  Visit: https://thetvdb.com/api-information
  Sign up and get your API key

TMDB API Key:
  Visit: https://www.themoviedb.org/settings/api
  Sign up and get your API key

RECOMMENDATION: Get both for best results!

3. SET API KEYS
---------------
Option A: Both APIs (recommended)
  export TVDB_API_KEY='your-tvdb-key-here'
  export TMDB_API_KEY='your-tmdb-key-here'

Option B: TVDB only
  export TVDB_API_KEY='your-tvdb-key-here'

Option C: TMDB only
  export TMDB_API_KEY='your-tmdb-key-here'

Option D: Via command line flags
  ./kodi-renamer -tvdb-key 'key1' -tmdb-key 'key2' -dir /path

4. TEST SCANNER (No API needed)
-------------------------------
# Build test utility
go build -o test-scanner ./cmd/test-scanner

# Create test files
mkdir test_files
cd test_files
touch "Breaking.Bad.S01E01.720p.mkv"
touch "The.Matrix.1999.1080p.mp4"
touch "Game.of.Thrones.S03E09.avi"
cd ..

# Run scanner test
./test-scanner -dir test_files

5. DRY RUN TEST (Requires at least one API key)
------------------------------------------------
# Test with both APIs
export TVDB_API_KEY='your-key'
export TMDB_API_KEY='your-key'
./kodi-renamer -dir test_files -dry-run

# Test with TVDB only
export TVDB_API_KEY='your-key'
unset TMDB_API_KEY
./kodi-renamer -dir test_files -dry-run

# Test with TMDB only
unset TVDB_API_KEY
export TMDB_API_KEY='your-key'
./kodi-renamer -dir test_files -dry-run

6. INTERACTIVE MODE (Requires at least one API key)
----------------------------------------------------
./kodi-renamer -dir test_files

7. AUTO MODE (Requires at least one API key)
---------------------------------------------
./kodi-renamer -dir test_files -auto -dry-run

8. REAL USAGE
-------------
# Always test first!
./kodi-renamer -dir /path/to/your/media -dry-run

# If satisfied, run for real
./kodi-renamer -dir /path/to/your/media

COMMON PATTERNS
---------------
Movies detected from:
  - Movie.Name.1999.1080p.mkv
  - Movie.Name.(2010).mp4
  - Movie.Name.[2015].avi

TV Series detected from:
  - Show.Name.S01E01.mkv
  - Show.Name.1x05.mp4
  - Show.Name.Season.1.Episode.3.avi

API BEHAVIOR
------------
Both APIs configured:
  - Searches both TVDB and TMDB
  - Results merged and displayed with [tvdb] or [tmdb] prefix
  - TVDB results shown first
  - More comprehensive results

One API configured:
  - Uses only that API
  - Faster operation
  - Still works great

No APIs configured:
  - Clear error message
  - Instructions to set at least one

TIPS
----
- Use -dry-run first ALWAYS
- Use -auto for batch processing
- Scanner works without API key for testing
- Files renamed in same directory
- Original extensions preserved
- Conflicts prevented automatically
- Both APIs = best coverage
- TMDB results sorted by popularity

TROUBLESHOOTING
---------------
Q: "At least one API key is required"
A: Set TVDB_API_KEY or TMDB_API_KEY (or both)
   export TVDB_API_KEY='your-key'
   export TMDB_API_KEY='your-key'

Q: "failed to authenticate with TVDB"
A: Check your TVDB API key is valid at thetvdb.com

Q: "failed to authenticate with TMDB" or 401 error
A: Check your TMDB API key is valid at themoviedb.org

Q: "No results found"
A: Try with both APIs for better coverage
   File will be skipped, try renaming manually first

Q: Scanner not detecting properly
A: Run test-scanner to see how files are parsed
   ./test-scanner -dir /path/to/files

Q: Go not found
A: Add Go to PATH: export PATH=$PATH:~/go/bin

Q: Want better results?
A: Use both APIs! More sources = better matches

EXAMPLES
--------
# Best setup (both APIs)
export TVDB_API_KEY='abc123'
export TMDB_API_KEY='xyz789'
./kodi-renamer -dir ~/Downloads -dry-run

# Quick test with one API
./kodi-renamer -tmdb-key 'xyz789' -dir ~/Downloads -dry-run

# Batch processing with both
export TVDB_API_KEY='abc123'
export TMDB_API_KEY='xyz789'
./kodi-renamer -dir /media/unsorted -auto

# Interactive with TVDB only
./kodi-renamer -tvdb-key 'abc123' -dir ~/Movies
